    <h2 class="sect-title">About Lincoln Park</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <h3>Lincoln Park</h3>
            <p class="par-lg">Located on a section of the former Royal Canadian Forces Base Calgary airfield during the World War II, Lincoln Park is a quiet and scenic residential neighborhood in South West Calgary. The neighborhood derives its name from a small military housing community that was reserved for the members of the US Air Force stationed at the airfield during the war.</p>

            <h3>Lincoln Park Real Estate</h3>
            <p class="par-lg">The community in Lincoln Park primarily consists of townhouses and apartment condominiums that are available for an average price of around $240,000. Given its close proximity to the Mount Royal College, a major chunk of the residents comprises of students living in rented properties. From the Westhills Towne Centre to Calgaryâ€™s largest indoor suburban mall, the Chinook Centre, the Lincoln Park real estate offers its residents ample facilities to shop for their everyday needs. Apart from this, there are abundant recreational facilities in Lincoln Park including the Richmond Green golf course, North Glenmore Park and Glenmore Athletic Park that houses a tennis court, ball court, swimming pool and even a skating rink.</p>

